---
export const prerender = true;

import FinalEngagement from '../../components/final-engagement.astro';
import Icon from '../../components/icon.astro';
import WhatsappButton from '../../components/whatsapp-button.astro';
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/main-layout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../../components/hero-section.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Website Performance Optimization"
  description="Optimize your website for speed, SEO, and user experience. Our performance optimization services will reduce load times and increase conversions, ensuring your site delivers results."
  keywords="website performance optimization, speed optimization, SEO optimization, improve site speed, boost conversions, web performance audit"
>
  <link
    rel="preload"
    href="/images/services/performance-optimization.webp"
    as="image"
    type="image/webp"
    slot="html-head"
  />
  <HeroSection image="services/performance-optimization">
    <p class="heading1 inverted">Boost Your Website's Speed and Performance</p>
    <p class="text-balance text-pretty-mobile">
      Don't lose customers to slow load times. Optimize your site for speed, better SEO, and higher conversions.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <button id="free-performance-audit-button" class="button" data-size="large" data-free-consultation>
        Start Your Performance Audit
      </button>
      <WhatsappButton />
    </div>
  </HeroSection>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <header>
        <p class="tagline">Speed Up. Scale Up.</p>
        <h1 class="heading2">Website Performance Optimization Services</h1>
      </header>
      <div class="even-columns slim-content one-column">
        <p class="body1 text-center text-balance text-pretty-mobile">
          Be it for streamlining mobile performance or optimizing for different countries, Mueller offers competent
          approaches that ensure the optimal performance of your site on any device and operating system. Including
          modern-day strategies such as code minification, image optimization, and enhancing server-side performance,
          our attainment of faster page load speeds, improved search results, and increased conversion rates are
          achieved.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section gradient-up">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <header>
        <p class="tagline">Speed Wins â€” Don't Be Left Behind</p>
        <h2 class="heading2">Why Performance Optimization Is a Game-Changer</h2>
      </header>
      <ul class="even-columns three-columns">
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <Icon name="flash" width="68" height="68" />
          <h3 class="heading3">Faster Load Times</h3>
          <p class="body2 text-balance text-pretty-mobile">Captivate users with sub-3-second page load times.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <Icon name="frontend-performance" width="68" height="68" />
          <h3 class="heading3">Boost SEO</h3>
          <p class="body2 text-balance text-pretty-mobile">
            Search engines rank faster sites higher, driving more organic traffic.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <Icon name="growth" width="68" height="68" />
          <h3 class="heading3">Higher Conversions</h3>
          <p class="body2 text-balance text-pretty-mobile">
            Fast sites increase user satisfaction and conversions by up to 10%.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <Icon name="target" width="68" height="68" />
          <h3 class="heading3">Lower Bounce Rates</h3>
          <p class="body2 text-balance text-pretty-mobile">Keep users engaged and reduce drop-offs.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <Icon name="scalable-architecture" width="68" height="68" />
          <h3 class="heading3">Scalability for Growth</h3>
          <p class="body2 text-balance text-pretty-mobile">Maintain top performance as traffic surges.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <Icon name="rocket" width="68" height="68" />
          <h3 class="heading3">Seamless User Experience</h3>
          <p class="body2 text-balance text-pretty-mobile">Delight visitors across all devices and platforms.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section primary">
    <div class="wrapper">
      <header>
        <p class="tagline inverted">The Fast Lane to Success</p>
        <h2 class="heading2 inverted">The Impact of Speed Optimization</h2>
      </header>
      <ul class="even-columns four-columns">
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <strong class="heading1 text-bold">7%</strong>
          <span class="body2 text-balance"> in conversions can be lost due to a 1-second delay.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <strong class="heading1 text-bold">10%</strong>
          <span class="body2 text-balance">
            boost in conversions can be achieved by improving load times by just 1 second.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <strong class="heading1 text-bold">80%</strong>
          <span class="body2 text-balance"> lower bounce rates are seen on sites that load in under 3 seconds.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="card white shadow align-center fade-from-bottom">
          <strong class="heading1 text-bold">25%</strong>
          <span class="body2 text-balance"> higher rankings are achieved by faster sites on search engines.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section wrapper">
    <header>
      <p class="tagline">Speed and Precision in Every Step</p>
      <h2 class="heading2">Our Proven Performance Optimization Process</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="even-columns three-columns">
      <li class="card white shadow align-left fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Audit & Analysis</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          Using industrial-leading tools and performance testing, we dig into every aspect of your site, identify
          bottlenecks and inefficiencies that lead to inferior performance, and review all page load times and server
          response times, script execution times, image sizes, and configurations of the server.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow align-left fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Code Refinement</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          Websites add unwanted or redundant code that makes the website take longer to load and generally less
          efficient. Our expert developers examine the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to pinpoint outdated or inefficient
          code.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow align-left fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Asset Compression</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          We have formulated techniques to compress larger images and videos, and greater script files-the most
          significant will be in slowing down the loading time on your page.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow align-left fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Caching Solutions</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          Seasoned experts in MUELLER Solutions implement advanced caching solutions at all levels of design, from
          browser caching to server-side caching and even reverse proxy caching, depending on your website's
          architecture.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow align-left fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">CDN Deployment</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          Using a CDN allows us to serve your website's assets from the nearest possible server to a user's geographic
          location, thereby minimizing latency and speeding up load times.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow align-left fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Real-Time Monitoring</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          We are at the top of identifying any issues about performance and taking care of them so they may not create
          troubles with your website's speed or reliability for you before they do for the users.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section class="section wrapper">
    <header>
      <p class="tagline">Got Questions? We've Got Answers.</p>
      <h2 class="heading2">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="even-columns slim-content one-column">
      <li class="card white shadow fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Why is website performance optimization important?</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          Faster sites usually render a great experience to visitors, foster engagement, and enhance search engine
          rankings. Google favors speed and contributes to higher conversion rates, making optimization the key to any
          effective digital strategy.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">How can I tell if my website needs optimization?</h3>
        <ul data-type="list" data-list-style="disc">
          <li>It takes more than 3 seconds for the pages to load.</li>
          <li>The bounce rate is high with poor engagements</li>
          <li>The performance on a mobile device is not so great</li>
          <li>The SEO rankings are low</li>
          <li>The system tends to crash or get timed out when traffic is huge and peak.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">How long does it take to optimize my website?</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          The time scale for optimization depends on the size and complexity of your website along with the scope of
          issues identified after a website audit.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">Will performance optimization affect my website's design or functionality?</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          No, our optimization methods will enhance your website's performance without changing any design elements of
          your site.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="card white shadow fade-from-bottom">
        <h3 class="heading3">How does website performance impact my SEO rankings?</h3>
        <p class="body1">
          Website performance is a great SEO factor that Google sees through the speed of the page as part of its rank
          signals. Your slow loads can penalize your ranking in search!
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <FinalEngagement
    title="Speed Up. Scale Up."
    description="Ready to Boost Your Website's Performance?"
    buttonText="Unlock Your Website's Full Potential"
  />
</MainLayout>
